Kauru and Kajuru Local Government Areas of Kaduna State, on Wednesday, signed a joint deal to promote harmony. NAN reports that agreement, signed in Kafanchan, was facilitated by the Centre For Humanitarian Dialogue to deepen peace building efforts. Cafra Caino, Kajuru LGA Chairman, pledged the council’s commitment to sustainable peace. He said the violence witnessed happened in Kajuru in 2019 and 2020 will be forever remembered. The chairman regretted that the crisis had created widows and orphans. “Part of our responsibility is to be partners in anything that will bring development and progress to the local government.” Caino said the intervention of the centre was timely and expressed gratitude for the intervention. He cautioned the people against taking laws into their hands and report their grievances through lawful means.